KafkaOauthDemo
===================

The Kafka OAuth demo shows how a customer can authenticate their client via OAuth2 to Kafka and how they can read data from a Kafka topic API and.

This is only a sample without support and liability to its correctness!

Prerequisite
------------

The code is based on .Net 5.0 and the Confluent.Kafka client (1.6.2), as well as the Newtonsoft.Json library (12.0.3) for JSON transformation.

Package Links:

* https://www.nuget.org/packages/Confluent.Kafka/
* https://www.nuget.org/packages/Newtonsoft.Json/

You need to download/add the packages to the nuget package manager.


How to use
----------

In order to use the sample please change the following parameters. Those parameters should previously send to you.

  ClientId = 'YOUR_CLIENT_ID'
  ClientSecret = 'YOUR_CLIENT_PWD'
  TokenUrl = 'OAUTH_TOKEN_API_URL'
  topicName = "TOPIC_NAME";
  BootstrapServers = "BROKER_URL"


You also need to provide the the CA certificate location. The certificate file must be in PEM format.

  CaLocation = 'cert.pem'

